<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2017/09/18/spring-cloud-data-flow-1-3-0-m2-released">Spring Cloud Data Flow 1.3.0.M2 released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/7881b619a0163626e6d7fefc7c43597d?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/grenfro">Glenn Renfro</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2017-09-18 13:40:00.0">September 18, 2017</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3030" href="/blog/2017/09/18/spring-cloud-data-flow-1-3-0-m2-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>We are pleased to announce the 1.3.0. M2 release of the Spring Cloud Data Flow and its associated ecosystem of projects.</p>
<p>Local Server: <a href="https://docs.spring.io/spring-cloud-dataflow/docs/1.3.0.M2/reference/htmlsingle/#getting-started">Getting Started Guide</a>.</p>
<h2><a href="#dashboard-flo" class="anchor" name="dashboard-flo"></a>Dashboard / Flo</h2>
<p>In this second installment of 1.3 release of Dashboard/Flo, we have addressed the core functionalities backing the streaming and task/batch operations. </p>
<p>Continuing the <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2017/08/07/spring-cloud-data-flow-1-3-0-m1-released">Angular4 based infrastructure upgrades</a>, the streaming and task/batch workflows now include the modern look and feel and are packed with usability improvements as well. </p>
</div>
</section>
